Great teacher, gives good lectures, assignment was straight forward and if you study the quiz is easy also.
Great prof! My favorite one yet! Its sad that for 1370 you only get him for 13 of the semester...

Teaches Module 1 for ADM1370. Great professor who is very clear, engaging, and funny. He is very approachable and there to answer questions. Although material is somewhat dry, he makes it interesting. Midterm and final was fair. Assignment was easy.

Teaches the wiki module for ADM1370. Ruhi, Raahemi, and his share their classes, so you'll get all 3 profs. His quizzes are hard though. Make sure to read the textbook because unlike the other modules, this one has a lot of information to take in. Overall, he's a decent prof.
Really great professor. Was interesting and kept the class engaged. His use of the textbook was good too, especially because his readings were short.

Dude was mad hype. Came on time for class and he taught his part of the course flawlessly. He made the class very interesting, and was a very funny individual. Thank you BasedGod for this opportunity. #BigBodyBugatti

He is a really nice guy,and funny sometimes. His class tho is really boring despite how much he tries to make it more fun. His quiz was really hard, and the material werent really from lectures and mostly from textbook stuff we didnt cover in class.

Excellent professor! His lectures are extremely interesting. The assignments and exams are fun and easy to do. Just have to love ADM1370. It's recommended that you collaborate/talk with other people throughout ADM1370. Also, study concepts and you will be ok. Sometimes, you don't need textbook, slides are great. Take notes.

Work with the people in your class and you'll all do great.

Overall... pretty decent professor. He is very knowledgeable in the material and he is an excellent lecturer.
